	<entry>
		<title>Lovecraftian Science</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://nightland.website/index.php/journal/30-news/248-lovecraftian-science"/>
		<published>2016-07-14T11:28:00+00:00</published>
		<updated>2016-07-14T11:28:00+00:00</updated>
		<id>https://nightland.website/index.php/journal/30-news/248-lovecraftian-science</id>
		<author>
			<name>Kate Coady</name>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;If I posted very much about H.P. Lovecraft, I could easily drown the weaker William Hope Hodgson signal. Nevertheless, most fans of Mr. Hodgson are also interested in Mr. Lovecraft's work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Considering the sort of discussion that used to take place on the Night Speech bulletin board, I think some of you will appreciate Fred Lubnow's &lt;a href=&quot;https://lovecraftianscience.wordpress.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Lovecraftian Science&lt;/a&gt; blog, in which he frequently considers Mr. Lovecraft's works from a scientific point of view.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He has published &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_ss_i_1_15?url=search-alias%3Dstripbooks&amp;amp;field-keywords=journal+of+lovecraftian+science&amp;amp;sprefix=undefined%2Caps%2C146&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Journal of Lovecraftian Science, Volume 1&lt;/a&gt; in paperback and ebook format, and is presently preparing Volume 2.&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;If I posted very much about H.P. Lovecraft, I could easily drown the weaker William Hope Hodgson signal. Nevertheless, most fans of Mr. Hodgson are also interested in Mr. Lovecraft's work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Considering the sort of discussion that used to take place on the Night Speech bulletin board, I think some of you will appreciate Fred Lubnow's &lt;a href=&quot;https://lovecraftianscience.wordpress.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Lovecraftian Science&lt;/a&gt; blog, in which he frequently considers Mr. Lovecraft's works from a scientific point of view.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He has published &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_ss_i_1_15?url=search-alias%3Dstripbooks&amp;amp;field-keywords=journal+of+lovecraftian+science&amp;amp;sprefix=undefined%2Caps%2C146&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Journal of Lovecraftian Science, Volume 1&lt;/a&gt; in paperback and ebook format, and is presently preparing Volume 2.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
		<category term="Lovecraftian Science" />
